@Node INTRODUCTION "GrabURL.guide/Introduction"

@{jcenter}@{u}@{b}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

@{jleft}GrabURL is an HTTP robot.

An HTTP robot is a program that can automatically download one or more files using HTTP.  Then it can scan those files to search for references to other files that it download upon some conditions and so on...

GrabURL is written in ARexx for a maximum flexibility.  It was made to fit @{b}my@{ub} needs.

You can create your own scripts using @{"GrabHTTP" Link GrabHTTP.guide/main 0}, @{"UrlManager" Link UrlManager.guide/main 0} and @{"ScanHTML" Link ScanHTML.guide/main 0}, simply consider GrabURL as a demo script.

@EndNode

@Node FEATURES "GrabURL.guide/Features"

@{jcenter}@{u}@{b}Features@{ub}@{uu}
@{jleft}@{lindent 4}@{pari -2}
@{par}- Use 3 'C' programs, which means QUICK compared with ARexx-only scripts
@{par}- Is ARexx, which means flexible compared with 'C' only programs.
@{par}- Give a lot of control to the user
@{par}- Puts the full URL in file's comment
@{par}- Just read this document to see what GrabURL has to offer.

@{pard}@{lindent 0}

@EndNode

